      "comment": "TOORAM DANNY (9) has come from wider on this row in both starts since a spell, filling a minor placing when resuming at Shepparton before working at his latest appearance. Building in fitness and is suited up to a distance where he has recorded a win and a placing in two attempts. MADAM REACTOR (1) drew a wide gate and worked last start so forgive that result. Gets the ace draw this time and led from wider when winning two back so has the speed to take advantage. OWEN THE SAINTS (11) should strip fitter so is a player after coming from a similar draw for a close second when resuming at Shepparton. IM DUSTEE (10) showed pleasing improvement last time out when third at Shepparton.",
